===Etymology 1===
From {{OE.}} ''truht'' ("trout"), in part from {{OF.}} ''[[truite]]'', from {{LL.}} ''[[tructa]]'', perhaps from {{Gk.}} {{term|τρώκτης|sc=Grek|tr=trōktēs||nibbler}}, from {{term|τρώγω|sc=Grek|tr=trōgō||to gnaw}}, from {{PIE.}} base ''*tere-'' ("to rub, to turn").

